This paper is primarily focused on the theoretical analysis of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper discusses the tradeoff between discrimination and generalization in GANs, which is a key issue in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of neural networks in GANs, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
